{"test":"vm-lifecycle-core-k3s","symptom":"loadFlannelSubnetEnv failed: open /run/flannel/subnet.env: no such file or directory","root_cause":"k3s flannel CNI race: pods scheduled before flannel control loop writes subnet.env. Usually self-heals via kubelet retry; occasionally stalls long enough that agent node never registers. Platform flake â€” not a rio-build bug.","fix_owner":"P0179","fix_description":"P0179's server-node-exists gate (b42a0af) + 600s budget (7c437e1) absorbs most occurrences by giving flannel init time. DISTINCT from airgap-timing (no loadFlannelSubnetEnv in log = wrong-gate bug, not this). [x2] prefix = nixbuild already retried once; one more local retry is the cap.","retry":"Once"}
{"test":"vm-lifecycle-autoscale-k3s","symptom":"nodes \"k3s-agent\" not found â€” waitReady timeout at server-node gate, NO loadFlannelSubnetEnv in log","root_cause":"Builder variance on airgap import. k3s imports images serially/alphabetically before kubelet starts; rio-controllerâ†’gatewayâ†’schedulerâ†’storeâ†’worker at ~25s/image typical, but 5Ă— slower builders observed (7c437e1). autoscale is the longest critical-path fragment (~14min) â†’ most susceptible to tail variance blowing the 600s gate.","fix_owner":"P0179","fix_description":"P0179 bumped gate 300sâ†’600s (7c437e1) tuned on observed tail (~170s agent import). If a >6Ă— slow builder shows up, gate blows â€” RERUN gets a different builder allocation. Structural fix would need a larger budget OR per-builder scaling, neither planned.","retry":"Once"}
{"test":"vm-lifecycle-ctrlrestart-k3s","symptom":"controller-restart subtest: phase=Building progress=0/1 at timeout â€” wait exceeds 120s under TCG","root_cause":"TCG dispatch lag. Post-bootstrap-fix, the controller-restart subtest's 30s-sleep build may not reach the worker within budget if flannel race self-healed but delayed pod startup. CR fields phase/progress are WATCH-TASK-PATCHED â€” stale if drain_stream reconnect hasn't fired. Check scheduler derivations_running for ground truth.","fix_owner":"P0179","fix_description":"P0179 bumped wait 60â†’120s (d874133) + added try/except diagnostic on both waits. Variance magnitude: build-crd-flow applyâ†’terminal observed 22sâ€“112s between identical runs (5Ă—). Budget covers observed tail; if 120s insufficient, cascade-delay from earlier subtest bootstrap is the likely cause.","retry":"Once"}
{"test":"vm-lifecycle-recovery-k3s","symptom":"recovery subtest timeout â€” sched_metric_wait exceeds 120s default on settle or dispatch","root_cause":"Flannel-race cascade into subtest timing. Bootstrap self-heals but delayed pod startup enough that subsequent subtests miss budget. Also: recovery kills scheduler leader â†’ new leader's recover_from_pg takes ~15-30s under coverage instrumentation; timing-sensitive.","fix_owner":"P0176","fix_description":"P0176 switched metric scrapes to apiserver pods/proxy (97f1305, no port-forward TIME_WAIT cascade) and bumped sched_metric_wait 60â†’120s (245a351). Retry cost ~200ms/attempt now vs ~3-5s before â€” variance was pf-induced, not application-induced. If this blows, it's a genuinely slow builder.","retry":"Once"}
{"test":"vm-lifecycle-reconnect-k3s","symptom":"loadFlannelSubnetEnv failed OR nodes k3s-agent not found at bootstrap","root_cause":"Same k3s flannel/airgap bootstrap surface as core-k3s. The reconnect-specific flake (Build CR phase:Unknown from NotFound retry-budget exhaust) was STRUCTURALLY FIXED in 1929c5d via sched_metric_wait for derivations_runningâ‰Ą1 on new leader â€” do NOT retry for that signature.","fix_owner":"P0179","fix_description":"P0179's sched_metric_wait gate (1929c5d) moves controller's retry window past the recovery race (validated 12/12). Only the bootstrap-level flannel/airgap variance remains retry-worthy. If phase:Unknown + build_watch_reconnects_total at MAX â†’ regression, hard-fail.","retry":"Once"}
{"test":"vm-le-stability-k3s","symptom":"loadFlannelSubnetEnv failed OR nodes k3s-agent not found at bootstrap","root_cause":"k3s flannel subnet race / airgap import builder variance at bootstrap. No leader-election-specific flake mode remains after P0176's failover-wait relaxation (7763b00: standby-wins is a fair race post-step_down; tx+1 is the sole invariant).","fix_owner":"P0179","fix_description":"P0179's server-node-exists gate + 600s airgap budget covers the bootstrap surface. The standby-wins assertion was structurally relaxed in 7763b00 (P0176) â€” if `new_leader == standby` fails, that's a regression of 7763b00, not a retry case.","retry":"Once"}
{"test":"vm-le-build-k3s","symptom":"build-during-failover dispatch wait timeout â€” derivations_running stays 0 beyond 120s after leader kill","root_cause":"Build-during-failover timing. Leader kill â†’ step_down â†’ fair race (standby 5s poll vs replacement ~3-5s cold-start). New leader's first dispatch Tick is 10s cadence; under TCG + coverage instrumentation, new-leader-ready to first-dispatch can exceed budget. kubectl-logs-grep was the OLD dispatch check â€” FIXED in P0176/P0179; now uses metrics.","fix_owner":"P0176","fix_description":"P0176 switched dispatch check to scheduler metrics via pods/proxy (095b94aâ†’97f1305) â€” kubelet http2 log-stream fragility no longer in the path. P0179 (96763b0) dropped log-grep entirely for cgroup state. If metrics-based check times out, it's genuine dispatch lag under TCG, not observation fragility.","retry":"Once"}
{"test":"vm-cli-k3s","symptom":"loadFlannelSubnetEnv failed OR nodes k3s-agent not found at bootstrap","root_cause":"k3s flannel/airgap bootstrap variance. cli scenario has no timing-sensitive subtests of its own â€” failures are always at the k3s-full fixture bootstrap. Coverage profraw collection race (7fd2f95) is a .#coverage-full issue, not .#ci.","fix_owner":"P0179","fix_description":"P0179's bootstrap gate covers this. cli-k3s is the shortest k3s test; least susceptible but shares the bootstrap surface. If this flakes while other k3s tests pass in the same .#ci run, it's builder allocation luck â€” RERUN.","retry":"Once"}
